e14f229a-4300-40c5-90bb-c51223b4fba8.02f02103-74d9-476d-894b-0c82843cf3b8.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Executes an Expression (e.x value1 \=\= value2)

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the value to threshold with
value2 - the threshold to threshold against
operator - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
okstring - string to push into returnResult if the threshold has not been passed
failedstring - string to push into the returnResult if the threshold has been passed

Responses\:
true - the expression is true
false - the expression is false

Pings the requested machine from the Web Services machine

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or IP address of the target host

Responses\:
passed - a successful connection was made
failure - unable to make a connection
host not found - could not resolve hostname to a valid IP address

Extra Results\:
output - raw output of the results
address - actual IP address pinged
% Packet Loss - The percentage of packets that ping replies were received for.
Average Latency - The average ping response time in milliseconds.
max latency - The maximum response time of all the pings (in milliseconds).
min latency - the minimum number of milliseconds it took to receive a ping response.

e14f229a-4300-40c5-90bb-c51223b4fba8.description=
Tests the connections to a given list of hosts.

Inputs\:
hosts - A list of hosts to test.
lossThreshold - The maximum % packet loss that is considered acceptable.
latencyThreshold - The maximum number of milliseconds of latency that are acceptable.
delimiter - A delimiter that separates the different hosts.
keyName - A key in which to hold the summary of the connection test.
display - If 'True' then the results will be displayed when the flow is finished.

Returns\:
A message listing hosts that have failed their connection tests.

Responses\:
success - All hosts passed test.
failure - one or more URLs failed the test.
